 {"id":"DIAL-n9j","title":"CI workflow for tests (unit, integration, e2e)","description":"# Description

GitHub Actions workflow that runs all test suites on every PR and push, with cross-platform support and detailed logging.

## Workflow File

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

env:
  CARGO_TERM_COLOR: always
  RUST_BACKTRACE: 1

jobs:
  check:
    name: Format & Lint
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable
        with:
          components: rustfmt, clippy

      - name: Cache cargo
        uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2

      - name: Check formatting
        run: cargo fmt --all -- --check

      - name: Run clippy
        run: cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings

  unit-tests:
    name: Unit Tests (${{ matrix.os }})
    needs: check
    strategy:
      fail-fast: false
      matrix:
        os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest, windows-latest]
    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable

      - name: Cache cargo
        uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2
        with:
          key: ${{ matrix.os }}

      - name: Install Linux dependencies
        if: runner.os == 'Linux'
        run: |
          sudo apt-get update
          sudo apt-get install -y libudev-dev libgtk-3-dev libappindicator3-dev libasound2-dev

      - name: Run unit tests
        run: cargo test --lib --verbose
        env:
          RUST_LOG: debug

      - name: Upload test logs on failure
        if: failure()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: unit-test-logs-${{ matrix.os }}
          path: |
            target/debug/.fingerprint/*/output
            **/*.log

  integration-tests:
    name: Integration Tests (${{ matrix.os }})
    needs: unit-tests
    strategy:
      fail-fast: false
      matrix:
        os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest, windows-latest]
    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable

      - name: Cache cargo
        uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2
        with:
          key: ${{ matrix.os }}-integration

      - name: Install Linux dependencies
        if: runner.os == 'Linux'
        run: |
          sudo apt-get update
          sudo apt-get install -y libudev-dev libgtk-3-dev libappindicator3-dev libasound2-dev

      - name: Run integration tests
        run: cargo test --test integration --verbose
        env:
          RUST_LOG: debug
          SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE: mock

      - name: Upload test logs on failure
        if: failure()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: integration-test-logs-${{ matrix.os }}
          path: |
            **/*.log
            target/debug/deps/*.log

  e2e-tests:
    name: E2E Tests (${{ matrix.os }})
    needs: integration-tests
    strategy:
      fail-fast: false
      matrix:
        os: [ubuntu-latest, macos-latest, windows-latest]
    runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable

      - name: Cache cargo
        uses: Swatinem/rust-cache@v2
        with:
          key: ${{ matrix.os }}-e2e

      - name: Install Linux dependencies
        if: runner.os == 'Linux'
        run: |
          sudo apt-get update
          sudo apt-get install -y libudev-dev libgtk-3-dev libappindicator3-dev libasound2-dev

      - name: Build release binary
        run: cargo build --release

      - name: Run E2E tests (Unix)
        if: runner.os != 'Windows'
        run: |
          chmod +x tests/e2e/*.sh
          ./tests/e2e/run_all.sh
        env:
          SURFACE_DIAL_BIN: ./target/release/surface-dial
          SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE: mock
          LOG_LEVEL: debug

      - name: Run E2E tests (Windows)
        if: runner.os == 'Windows'
        shell: pwsh
        run: |
          $env:SURFACE_DIAL_BIN = ".\target\release\surface-dial.exe"
          $env:SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE = "mock"
          $env:LOG_LEVEL = "debug"
          .\tests\e2e\run_all.ps1

      - name: Upload E2E test logs
        if: always()
        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
        with:
          name: e2e-test-logs-${{ matrix.os }}
          path: |
            tests/e2e/logs/
            /tmp/surface-dial-test-*.log

  coverage:
    name: Code Coverage
    needs: unit-tests
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install Rust
        uses: dtolnay/rust-action@stable
        with:
          components: llvm-tools-preview

      - name: Install cargo-llvm-cov
        uses: taiki-e/install-action@cargo-llvm-cov

      - name: Install Linux dependencies
        run: |
          sudo apt-get update
          sudo apt-get install -y libudev-dev libgtk-3-dev libappindicator3-dev libasound2-dev

      - name: Generate coverage report
        run: cargo llvm-cov --all-features --lcov --output-path lcov.info

      - name: Upload to Codecov
        uses: codecov/codecov-action@v4
        with:
          files: lcov.info
          fail_ci_if_error: true
          token: ${{ secrets.CODECOV_TOKEN }}

  all-tests:
    name: All Tests Pass
    needs: [check, unit-tests, integration-tests, e2e-tests]
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: All tests passed
        run: echo "All test suites passed successfully!"
```

## Test Matrix

| Test Type | macOS | Linux | Windows | Description |
|-----------|:-----:|:-----:|:-------:|-------------|
| Format/Lint | - | ✓ | - | cargo fmt + clippy |
| Unit Tests | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | Library tests with mocking |
| Integration | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | HID simulation tests |
| E2E Tests | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | Full binary tests |
| Coverage | - | ✓ | - | Code coverage report |

## Key Features

1. **fail-fast: false** - Continue testing other platforms on failure
2. **Rust caching** - Swatinem/rust-cache for faster CI runs
3. **Test log upload** - Artifacts on failure for debugging
4. **Codecov integration** - Track coverage over time
5. **Mock mode** - Tests run without physical hardware
6. **Detailed logging** - RUST_LOG=debug for troubleshooting

## Branch Protection Settings

Configure in GitHub repository settings:
- Require status checks: `check`, `all-tests`
- Require branches to be up to date
- Require linear history (recommended)

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE=mock` | Run with mock HID device |
| `RUST_LOG=debug` | Verbose logging |
| `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` | Full backtraces on panic |

## Files to Create

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` - Main CI workflow

## Dependencies

- Unit tests (DIAL-blk) - for unit test job
- Integration tests (DIAL-ifk) - for integration job  
- E2E tests (DIAL-ikn) - for E2E job

## Testing Requirements

### Verify CI Locally
```bash
# Format check
cargo fmt --all -- --check

# Clippy
cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings

# Unit tests
cargo test --lib

# Integration tests
SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE=mock cargo test --test integration

# E2E tests
SURFACE_DIAL_TEST_MODE=mock ./tests/e2e/run_all.sh
```

## Success Criteria

- [ ] CI runs on every PR and push to main
- [ ] All three platforms tested (macOS, Linux, Windows)
- [ ] Test logs uploaded on failure
- [ ] Coverage report generated and uploaded
- [ ] Branch protection requires passing CI
- [ ] Mock mode allows tests without hardware
- [ ] < 15 minute total CI time

